|WKBSYNTAX
======

|CKBgearcheck|WKB
|CKBgearcheck <item>|WKB
|CKBupgrades|WKB

DESCRIPTION
===========

|YKOCompares the equipment in your inventory with the equipment you are
currently using. It accounts for weapon class, armour protection, equipment
stats, resistances, sigils, known combat effects, cyberware strain, durability,
and the equipment slots that an item would replace.

The normal report shows every comparable item, including upgrades, sidegrades,
downgrades, and items with effects that cannot be scored confidently. Use
|YKBgearcheck <item>|YKO for the full numeric breakdown.

Ranked equipment also shows its item level. Item level describes the part of
the game's progression for which the equipment was designed; it does not
prevent a lower-level character from using the item. Ranked weapons penetrate
some worn armour, while ranked armour resists weapons below its own level.
Equal-level weapon and armour ratings cancel each other.

When you have an empty equipment slot, gearcheck shows a separate
|GKB➕ EMPTY SLOT|YKO section and recommends the strongest compatible item in
your inventory. For ring and amulet slots, it can show multiple choices when
more than one slot is open.

|GKB🟢 UPGRADE|YKO means the carried item is measurably stronger.
|YKB🟡 SAME POWER (SIDEGRADE)|YKO means its overall score is close, but its
strengths may be distributed differently.
|RKB🔴 DOWNGRADE|YKO means the currently equipped item or loadout is stronger.
|YKB⚠ UNCERTAIN|YKO means an item has a scripted effect that cannot be scored
until its builder declares a power value.

Gearcheck never equips, removes, installs, or otherwise changes an item.
Scripted item effects are only included when the item explicitly declares
their power value.
